.TH DRY\-RUN\-DIFF 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
dry\-run\-diff.sh \- show colored diff of current state vs desired state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dry\-run\-diff.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compares the current machine state against the desired profile configuration
and displays a colored diff of the differences. Shows which packages would
be installed or removed, which dotfile symlinks would be created or updated,
and which services would be started. No changes are made to the system.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Profile to diff against.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success (diff displayed regardless of whether differences exist).
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid profile, unreadable configuration).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show diff for the full profile:
.B dry\-run\-diff.sh \-\-profile full
.TP
Show diff for a custom profile:
.B dry\-run\-diff.sh \-\-profile mysetup
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
